**Sorry**&nbsp;can be an admission that we've done the wrong thing, so use it carefully. Use it only if the message that we're communicating would sound abrupt or rude without it.

```jsx
<div>
<h4 className="typography-body-10 text-muted mb-3">For example:</h4>
<p className="typography-body-10 mb-2 ml-4"><span className="text-success font-bold">Do:</span> You’ve reached the maximum number of applications.</p>
<p className="typography-body-10 ml-4"><span className="text-danger font-bold">Don't:</span> Sorry, you’ve reached the maximum number of applications.</p>
</div>
```
